    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-02-27T15:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-02-27T15:54:00-05:00" n="408"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> files, lot 53 D 413:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to the
                        Commander in Chief Far East (<persName corresp="#p_CGMW1" type="to"
                            >Clark</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-02-27T15:54:00-05:00"
                            >February 27, 1953—3:54 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 932457. From <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                        >JCS</gloss> reur C 61283.<note n="1" xml:id="d408fn1">In this telegram,
                        Feb. 19, 1953, <persName corresp="#p_CGMW1">Clark</persName> concurred with
                        the views of the <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> as set forth in
                        paragraph 2 of <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 931311, Feb. 13, <ref
                            target="#pg_776">p. 776</ref>, and included a proposed letter announcing
                        to the Communists his intention to remove the immunity of the Kaesong and
                        Munsan-ni restricted areas, should that decision be made in Washington.
                            (<persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> files, lot 53 D
                        413)</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0835" n="801" xml:id="pg_801"/>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Re part 1. Comment on statement withheld pending final dec to implement
                        course of action outlined in para 2 of <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>
                            931311.<note n="2" xml:id="d408fn2">See <ref target="#d408fn1">footnote
                                1</ref>, above.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Re part 2. To facilitate diplomatic consultation State has queried <gloss
                            target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> re possibility obtaining pertinent oblique
                        aerial photos of Kaesong area as documentation for charges of Commie
                        buildup. If you have available oblique photos with appropriate interpretive
                        notations indicating location of mil facilities that would be useful this
                        purpose, request they be provided <gloss target="#t_ASAP1"
                        >ASAP</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Re part 3. Statement approved subject to deletion first sentence para E
                        and words “tolerated this military buildup and” in second sentence of same
                        para.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
